{
  "name": "Kalshi Market Scorer",
  "description": "A Python system that scores live Kalshi prediction-market contracts for trade ideas, pulling signals from many sources (weather/GEFS ensembles, polls/FiveThirtyEight, Polymarket prices and whale wallets, X/Twitter via Grok, sportsbook odds, order-flow microstructure, GDELT mentions base rates, Love Island teasers), scoring edge deterministically, then applying adversarial challenge and Kelly risk sizing before publishing ideas to a FastAPI dashboard. It also places and cancels Kalshi orders (demo by default; prod gated) and manages open positions. Note: this project has over 100 source files; consider scoping analysis to a subdirectory for faster results.",
